Package de.oth.blocklib.networking.messages

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AnimationMessage
    Contains information about the animation a model is currently doing
    BlockChangedMessage
    Contains the info which Block was changed
    ChatMessage
    Message used to send chat messages.
    ChunkMessage
    Contains the serialized informations about a chunk
    ChunkRequestMessage
    A message to request a chunk at the server that was not yet generated
    ClientIdMessage
    Part of the three way handshake between the server and the client.
    Server sends the client id and the client answers to acknowledge and start the spawn
    CommandMessage
    Message made to transport commands from other participants of the network
    EntityDespawnMessage
    Message about an entity despawning
    EntityInfoMessage
    Requests informations for a new connected client about existing entities in the world
    FluidSpawnedMessage
    Contains the informations about a new fluid spawn
    HealthUpdateMessage
    Communicates updates of NPC health
    JoinedMessage
    Initial message send by a client to the server immediately after the connection process.
    KillClientMessage
    A message from a client to the server to kill (currently kick) a client
    MessageRegistry  
    NpcSpawnedMessage
    Info about spawning Npcs
    NpcUpdateMessage
    Constantly sent messages from clientside to update Npc-positions
    PingMessage  
    PlayerSpawnedMessage
    A message send by the server to all clients when a new client connects to the server.
    Contains the avatar id and the nickname
    SaveMessage
    Message sent by a client to server to initialize server' shutdown or save.
    WorldItemSpawnedMessage
    Contains the info about a new item (e.g. spawned by breaking a Block)
